<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1725" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1725">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/52.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Answering your telegram April 7. Panaman Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            to-day states that he will have conference with Secretary of Government
                            and Justice, judge, and attorney of the Supreme <pb facs="1103" n="987" xml:id="pg_987"/> Court, without further delay, for the purpose of
                            hastening proceedings. He promised to do this last Tuesday. He adds
                            assurance of strict justice being decreed in accordance with law and the
                            practice of civilization.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>